eventData.headline: Rural Students Alliance at Yale
eventData.description:
Recognizing that students from small towns and rural communities have particular experiences that are unique from their urban peers and impact the way they experience Yale, the Rural Students Alliance of Yale is a group for rural students at Yale to get to know and support one another with the goal of improving the experience of rural students at Yale. We also aim to increase the visibility of rurality on Yale’s campus, not only highlighting rural members of its student body but also increasing the presence of rurality in academic inquiry through guest speakers, panels, film screenings, and more.

Come meet the Rural Students Alliance at Yale! We are an organization that aims to create a community of support for students transitioning to Yale coming from the small town life, while also discussing our own identity and issues impacting rural areas worldwide.

eventData.headline: First-Gen, Low-Income Advocacy Movement
eventData.description:
Student Org Event: Yale First-Generation and/or Low-Income Advocacy Movement

We are a coalition dedicated to advocacy and community-building for all First-generation and/or low-income students at Yale!

Throughout the year, we form task forces based on the projects that members want to work on, such as FGLI student-faculty mixers, financial aid literacy, and advocating for a FGLI-dedicated space on campus. In the midst of all of this advocacy, we also make sure to foster a safe space for FGLI folks to bond and form deeper relationships - if we don't support each other, who will?

Come meet the FAM! Join YFAM to meet fellow First-Generation and/or Low-Income students for an informal discussion about what it means to be FGLI at Yale.
Discussion will cover important resources, tips, and strategies for success.

eventData.headline: Yale Out of the Blue
eventData.description:
Out of the Blue is Yale University's award-winning contemporary A Cappella group, known for its tight vocals and electric performance style. Founded in 1986 by a group of eight students determined to create a new brand of "Yale A Cappella," Out of the Blue (OOTB, pronounced OOT-bah) has evolved into Yale's most dynamic vocal group, entertaining audiences near and far with an eclectic repertoire of current and classic pop, rock, R&B, jazz, and dubstep.

Come and hang out with Yale Out Of The Blue and get to know us! Information on Yale a cappella, rush and recruitment, as well as zoom fun and games!

eventData.headline: Military History Society
eventData.description:
“A strategy, even a great one, doesn't implement itself”
We’re the Yale Military History Society - a group of friends who are heavily interested in learning
about military strategy and military history through playing strategy games, wargames, and having
other events including discussions, speaker events, and travelling to battle sites.

Come one, come all to the YMHS’ Military History trivia night.  We’ll be hosting a house-written game of Jeopardy spanning military history from the ancients through today.  There’s no need to stay for the entire game, and feel free to pop in and out as your schedule permits.  We hope to see you there!

eventData.headline: Yale Mock Trial Association
eventData.description:
Mock trial is a mix of debate, theatre, and law that's wholly unique and very fun!  Every year we try cases, providing both attorneys and witnesses to compete against other universities across the nation.  Besides having one of the most competitive programs in the country, the YMTA also has an amazing community that feels like family.

We'll demonstrate some of what we do at our tournaments and open up to questions.

eventData.headline: Yale Adventist Campus Fellowship
eventData.description:
We are a Seventh-day Adventist Christian Student Organization that serves as an affinity group for Seventh-day Adventist students both at Yale and in the New Haven Area. We organize worship and ministry efforts with local congregations, network with Adventist students around the world, coordinate community service projects in the New Haven Area, and work with other campus organizations, religious and secular, on matters of justice.

Friday Evening Bible Study! Join us as we read through the book of Judges and discuss what we can learn from the example of Israel’s earliest days. No prior biblical knowledge necessary. We will also have time for prayer, testimonies, as well as plenty of time for you to meet other Adventists on campus.

eventData.headline: Kesem at Yale
eventData.description:
Kesem is a national non profit organization that provides a community for children whose parents suffer from cancer. Every summer we provide a free week long sleepaway summer camp for over 150+ kids aged 6 - 18 with 70+ student counselors. Throughout the year we plan for camp, fundraise for our kids, and host reunions.  Here is a video that gives you a little taste of camp magic from our 2018 Summer Camp Session: https://www.facebook.com/1410870739124866/videos/971525466352611 !

Join us for an hour of zoom filled fun where we'll be playing online games, listening to music, and sharing some silly camp memories! We can't wait to meet you all!
